  "prompt": "How can I get a near-perfect SAT score by studying for 4 days?",
  "response": "Achieving a near-perfect SAT score in just four days is a significant challenge, but with focused and strategic studying, you can maximize your potential. Here\u2019s a suggested plan:\n\n### Day 1: Familiarization and Diagnostic Testing\n1. **Understand the SAT Structure**: Familiarize yourself with the test sections\u2014Reading, Writing and Language, Math (No Calculator), and Math (Calculator).\n2. **Take a Diagnostic Test**: Take a full-length practice SAT under timed conditions to identify your strengths and weaknesses.\n3. **Review Your Results**: Analyze which sections and types of questions you struggled with the most. Focus your study more on these areas in the next few days.\n\n### Day 2: Targeted Study\n1. **Reading and Writing**:\n   - Focus on understanding the question types (e.g., evidence-based questions, grammar rules).\n   - Practice with passages and questions. Use high-quality resources like the College Board\u2019s official practice materials or reputable prep books.\n   - Take note of common traps and strategies for answering different question types.\n\n2. **Math**:\n   - Review key math concepts and formulas that are frequently tested (algebra, problem-solving, data analysis, advanced math).\n   - Practice specific question types, particularly those you struggled with on the diagnostic.\n\n### Day 3: Practice Tests and Review\n1. **Take Sectional Practice Tests**: Focus individually on the Reading, Writing, and Mathematics sections. \n   - Time yourself to simulate real testing conditions.\n   - After each section, review incorrect answers and understand why you got them wrong.\n\n2. **Review Key Strategies**:\n   - For Reading: Work on pacing and identify strategies for skimming passages for main ideas.\n   - For Writing: Focus on the grammar rules and rhetorical skills tested.\n   - For Math: Work on time-saving techniques and shortcuts.\n\n### Day 4: Full-Length Practice Test and Final Review\n1. **Take a Full-Length Practice Test**: Aim to simulate the actual test experience as closely as possible.\n   - Follow timing strictly, including breaks.\n   - Review your answers thoroughly.\n\n2. **Final Review**:\n   - Focus on your most recent mistakes and practice similar questions.\n   - Go over any math formulas or grammatical rules you're unsure of.\n   - Relax and ensure you get enough sleep before the actual test day.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Use Quality Resources**: Stick to official materials from the College Board or reputable prep companies.\n- **Stay Focused**: Minimize distractions and focus intensely during your study blocks.\n- **Practice Time Management**: During practice tests, learn to manage your time effectively to ensure you complete all sections.\n- **Self-Care**: Ensure you eat well, stay hydrated, and get adequate sleep, especially the night before the test.\n\nRemember, while four days is a short time frame, a focused and strategic approach can help you improve significantly. Good luck!",
